    The response to a UnregisterTerminalRequest. The parameters of the UnregisterTerminalResponse are:

    UnregisterTerminalResponse Parameters
    device Always provided The identifier of the device. Type is SubjectDeviceID.
    code Always provided The code indicates either success or failure. If the code is equal to com.avaya.csta.registration.RegistrationConstants.NORMAL_UNREGISTER or com.avaya.csta.registration.RegistrationConstants.CLIENT_REQUESTED_UNREG, then the unregistration was successful, otherwise it will contain an error code. For java developers using the sdk, a complete list of code values can be found in com.avaya.csta.registration.RegistrationConstants.
    reason Only provided with negative response. Indicates the reason for a failed unregistration if the code is neither equal to RegistrationConstants.NORMAL_UNREGISTER nor equal to RegistrationConstants.CLIENT_REQUESTED_UNREG.
